A U.S. Marine accused of killing a transgender Filipina appeared in court for the first time Friday to ask a court in the Philippines to downgrade his murder charge.

The Marine, Joseph Scott Pemberton, is being held at a
U.S. facility at the main Philippine army base — charged with the murder of Jennifer Laude who was found dead on Oct. 11 in a
hotel in Olongapo City, northwest of Manila.

Philippine government officials say Pemberton attacked Laude in a motel room after finding out she was a transgender woman.

She had apparently been strangled and drowned in a toilet bowl. 

